Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.58,0:17:27.54,English,,0,0,0,,that they were perhaps tricked by Socrates.\N{\rChinese}那时他们可能被苏格拉底斯骗了。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.84,0:17:30.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Socrates was 70 years old.\N{\rChinese}好的？苏格拉底斯70岁了。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.48,0:17:33.74,English,,0,0,0,,That's very old for back then, okay?\N{\rChinese}那时很久以前，算吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.90,0:17:38.16,English,,0,0,0,,70 years old was probably the age limit back then.\N{\rChinese}70岁时，可能是当时的年龄上限。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.36,0:17:39.80,English,,0,0,0,,He really didn't have much to live for.\N{\rChinese}他真的没什么可活的了。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.80,0:17:45.66,English,,0,0,0,,And here was the opportunity for Socrates to be a martyr for the truth,\N{\rChinese}他在此时刻…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.80,0:17:47.56,English,,0,0,0,,right? All his life,\N{\rChinese}右？他一生都在尝试说服人们民主没用。
